    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-28">August 28,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1406. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Acheson</hi>: Admiral Cooke and I have discussed
                    at length the matter set forth in your message relayed to me by Colonel
                        Carter.<note n="49" xml:id="d576fn49">Telegram No. 98402, August 23, <ref
                            target="#pg_871">p. 871</ref>.</note> I approved his plan which is
                    similar to the one apparently mentioned to you by the Secretary of Navy.<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d576fn50">James Forrestal.</note> Further than this I
                    authorized Admiral Cooke to begin turning over train convoys and bridge guards
                    at an early date so as to obligate national forces to assume these duties. This
                    will accomplish a double purpose.</p>
                <p>The Marines will be relieved of some of their present functions thus permitting
                    their concentration. At the same time this will require available national
                    forces recently arrived in Chinwangtao and due for Manchuria to dispose
                    southward instead of northward into Jehol and Manchuria which I am convinced
                    will arouse serious Communist reactions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
